##This is mom, your fighting mom

Micro-signal Yeguangbeifukan

Function introduction the supplement of Xinmin Evening News, founded on May 1,1946, is the oldest comprehensive supplement of Chinese newspapers.

I called my son to look at the picture, and he said, "who is this? " I said, "this is mom, your fighting mom. "

Today is the International Women's Day of "March 8" , pay tribute to all the women who fought in the front line of the fight against the plague!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the morning of January 21st, i suddenly received a wechat message from her: "Hello, head nurses! "! Due to the severe situation of the prevention and control of coronavirus, one person from each department is required to support the emergency and fever clinic. Two patients were transferred from wards closed during the holidays. Please send the name and contact information of the supporting nurse to the Nursing Information Collection Cluster by 12:00 today (January 21) , and request the supporting staff to be in place this afternoon!"

In this copy of the words below, she wrote: "This year, too bad! " In fact, we have been married ten years where a good New Year Ah. As an oncology ward nurse, her annual leave was sliced and diced. Only on the eve of New Year's Eve, some patients go home to rest, the two wards after the merger, their nurses can take a short shift leave. So, every year, she could only stay with me for a day or two, and then she would have to go back to work. As a person who has experienced SARS, I have been closely following the epidemic since early January, and my comments, especially after Zhong Nanshan arrived in Wuhan, have made me fully aware of the severity of the epidemic. So after receiving her wechat message, I almost did not hesitate to reply: "You resolutely do not go, very dangerous! "

When I said that, I wasn't ashamed, and I didn't think about who should go, and who would have to go in the end. I just don't think my son's mother can go. My best friend, who had SARS and spent two months in two hospitals, later described to me in detail the hard work of a nurse. Although the past 17 years, but I remember his words clearly: "their protective clothing wet, sweat on the breast, the same water. "

Will my wife be like this in the future?

She's been chosen. "I'll go, " she said. There was no hint of emotion. I can't imagine what her mind went through.

She added, "you can Carpool with your son tomorrow. " So be it.

Her hospital is in the top three of the list of ambulatory fever clinics. It was her battlefield, and she would defend a hot corner of it with a body heat gun.

From the 25th to the 28th, there was no news from her, and my reply was always washing my face, cooking, sweeping and sleeping. When the wechat video came on, she sat under an old bookcase on the balcony of her home, a slightly secret smile on an already over-familiar face. I know where her secret joy comes from. Fifteen years into her medical career, she never took a full week off! But this emergency preparedness, which initially made her nervous, almost made her a dream -- as if she were lying in bed for a week watching Ode to Joy.

On January 29, she finally entered the emergency fever pre-screening triage schedule, the battle she was facing had only just begun.

On This Day, I always think of a sentence she said: "compared with the people in our hospital who went to Hubei Province to support the epidemic area, I am nothing at all! " Above is a group photo of 15 members of their hospital's Hubei Support Team. Her male and female colleagues, carrying a national flag to the affected area, went to Xiantao, Qianjiang and Tianmen, along with the entire Shanxi medical team.

On This Day, I remembered a word I said to her: "You are not a hero, but you are fighting with a hero! "

At 7:50 in the morning, she sent a "military photo" as I asked. I'M GONNA check to see if she's well protected. In the photo, all she has is a pair of glasses behind her eyes, a blue bucket hat, a blue protective suit, a white surgical mask covering her face, and white nurse's shoes.

I called my son to see the photo and he asked, "who is this? "

I said, "this is mommy, your fighting mommy. "
